The President met with representatives from the National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC) to discuss the implementation of the Affordable Care Act and other insurance-related issues. They discussed the role of insurance commissioners in protecting consumers and promoting competitive health insurance markets. They also talked about making sure consumers understand their options and rights under the Affordable Care Act. The President mentioned the option for states to allow insurers to renew existing plans in 2014, as well as the importance of providing clear information to consumers about consumer protections and possible tax credits. The President expressed interest in hearing any ideas that insurance commissioners may have to ensure that Americans have access to affordable, quality coverage.